data.chText: （古代用于战斗或比赛的）双轮敞篷马车
data.enText: an open vehicle with two wheels, pulled by horses, used in ancient times in battle and for racing

means: (古代用于战斗或比赛的)双轮敞篷马车

tr: a light four-wheel horse-drawn ceremonial carriage
used in war and races in ancient Egypt and Greece and Rome

value.def: In ancient times, chariots were fast-moving vehicles with two wheels that were pulled by horses.
